defs.docs: # How to use cpal

defs.name: I16
defs.docs: The value 0 corresponds to 0.

defs.name: U16
defs.docs: The value 0 corresponds to 32768.

defs.name: F32
defs.docs: The boundaries are (-1.0, 1.0).

defs.name: SampleFormat
defs.docs: Format that each sample has.

defs.name: sample_size
defs.docs: Returns the size in bytes of a sample of this format.

defs.name: get_sample_size
defs.docs: Deprecated. Use `sample_size` instead.

defs.name: Sample
defs.docs: Trait for containers that contain PCM data.

defs.name: get_format
defs.docs: Returns the `SampleFormat` corresponding to this data type.

defs.name: to_f32
defs.docs: Turns the sample into its equivalent as a floating-point.

defs.name: to_i16
defs.docs: Converts this sample into a standard i16 sample.

defs.name: to_u16
defs.docs: Converts this sample into a standard u16 sample.

defs.name: from
defs.docs: Converts any sample type to this one by calling `to_i16`, `to_u16` or `to_f32`.

defs.name: Device
defs.docs: An opaque type that identifies a device that is capable of either audio input or output.

defs.name: EventLoop
defs.docs: Collection of voices managed together.

defs.name: StreamId
defs.docs: Identifier of a stream within the `EventLoop`.

defs.name: ChannelCount
defs.docs: Number of channels.

defs.name: SampleRate
defs.docs: The number of samples processed per second for a single channel of audio.

defs.name: Format
defs.docs: The format of an input or output audio stream.

defs.name: SupportedFormat
defs.docs: Describes a range of supported stream formats.

defs.name: min_sample_rate
defs.docs: Minimum value for the samples rate of the supported formats.

defs.name: max_sample_rate
defs.docs: Maximum value for the samples rate of the supported formats.

defs.name: data_type
defs.docs: Type of data expected by the device.

defs.name: StreamData
defs.docs: Stream data passed to the `EventLoop::run` callback.

defs.name: InputBuffer
defs.docs: Represents a buffer containing audio data that may be read.

defs.name: OutputBuffer
defs.docs: Represents a buffer that must be filled with audio data.

defs.name: U16
defs.docs: Samples whose format is `u16`.

defs.name: I16
defs.docs: Samples whose format is `i16`.

defs.name: F32
defs.docs: Samples whose format is `f32`.

defs.name: UnknownTypeInputBuffer
defs.docs: This is the struct that is provided to you by cpal when you want to read samples from a buffer.

defs.name: U16
defs.docs: Samples whose format is `u16`.

defs.name: I16
defs.docs: Samples whose format is `i16`.

defs.name: F32
defs.docs: Samples whose format is `f32`.

defs.name: UnknownTypeOutputBuffer
defs.docs: This is the struct that is provided to you by cpal when you want to write samples to a buffer.

defs.name: Devices
defs.docs: An iterator yielding all `Device`s currently available to the system.

defs.name: InputDevices
defs.docs: A `Devices` yielding only *input* devices.

defs.name: OutputDevices
defs.docs: A `Devices` yielding only *output* devices.

defs.name: SupportedInputFormats
defs.docs: An iterator that produces a list of input stream formats supported by the device.

defs.name: SupportedOutputFormats
defs.docs: An iterator that produces a list of output stream formats supported by the device.

defs.name: DeviceNotAvailable
defs.docs:
The device no longer exists. This can happen if the device is disconnected while the
 program is running.

defs.name: FormatsEnumerationError
defs.docs: Error that can happen when enumerating the list of supported formats.

defs.name: DeviceNotAvailable
defs.docs:
The device no longer exists. This can happen if the device is disconnected while the
 program is running.

defs.name: StreamTypeNotSupported
defs.docs: Returned if e.g. the default input format was requested on an output-only audio device.

defs.name: DefaultFormatError
defs.docs: May occur when attempting to request the default input or output stream format from a `Device`.

defs.name: DeviceNotAvailable
defs.docs:
The device no longer exists. This can happen if the device is disconnected while the
 program is running.

defs.name: FormatNotSupported
defs.docs: The required format is not supported.

defs.name: CreationError
defs.docs: Error that can happen when creating a `Voice`.

defs.name: devices
defs.docs: An iterator yielding all `Device`s currently available to the system.

defs.name: input_devices
defs.docs:
An iterator yielding all `Device`s currently available to the system that support one or more
 input stream formats.

defs.name: output_devices
defs.docs:
An iterator yielding all `Device`s currently available to the system that support one or more
 output stream formats.

defs.name: default_input_device
defs.docs: The default input audio device on the system.

defs.name: default_output_device
defs.docs: The default output audio device on the system.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: The human-readable name of the device.

defs.name: supported_input_formats
defs.docs: An iterator yielding formats that are supported by the backend.

defs.name: supported_output_formats
defs.docs: An iterator yielding output stream formats that are supported by the device.

defs.name: default_input_format
defs.docs: The default input stream format for the device.

defs.name: default_output_format
defs.docs: The default output stream format for the device.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Initializes a new events loop.

defs.name: build_input_stream
defs.docs: Creates a new input stream that will run from the given device and with the given format.

defs.name: build_output_stream
defs.docs: Creates a new output stream that will play on the given device and with the given format.

defs.name: play_stream
defs.docs: Instructs the audio device that it should start playing the stream with the given ID.

defs.name: pause_stream
defs.docs: Instructs the audio device that it should stop playing the stream with the given ID.

defs.name: destroy_stream
defs.docs: Destroys an existing stream.

defs.name: run
defs.docs: Takes control of the current thread and begins the stream processing.

defs.name: with_max_sample_rate
defs.docs: Turns this `SupportedFormat` into a `Format` corresponding to the maximum samples rate.

defs.name: cmp_default_heuristics
defs.docs:
A comparison function which compares two `SupportedFormat`s in terms of their priority of
 use as a default stream format.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the length of the buffer in number of samples.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the length of the buffer in number of samples.
